---
import OrbitalDiagram from "./OrbitalDiagram.astro";
---

<section
  class="bg-dark lg:direction-reverse grid grid-cols-1 gap-18 px-5 py-13 md:px-10 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:px-12.75 lg:py-20"
>
  <div class="order-last lg:order-first">
    <h2 class="font-sans text-3xl leading-tight text-white md:text-5xl">
      Why my perspective
    </h2>

    <h2 class="font-sans text-3xl leading-tight text-white md:text-5xl">
      <em class="font-bold text-[#E8A07A] italic">is different?</em>
    </h2>

    <div class="mt-10 items-start gap-10 md:mt-15 md:gap-15">
      <div>
        <p
          class="font-heading mb-6 text-base leading-[1.85] font-light text-white/80"
        >
          Cross-domain lens from <strong class="font-bold"
            >gaming, academia, government, and international development,</strong
          > simultaneously.
        </p>

        <div class="border-orange mb-6 border-l-2 pl-4 md:pl-6">
          <p
            class="font-heading text-base leading-[1.55] font-light text-white md:text-[21.6px]"
          >
            My specialty is turning complex problems into
            <strong>simple, functional, and memorable solutions.</strong>
          </p>
        </div>

        <p
          class="font-heading mb-6 text-base leading-[1.85] font-light text-white/80"
        >
          I’m drawn to opportunities where strategy needs empathy, systems need
          clarity, and digital products need to <strong class="font-bold">
            serve real people, not just requirements</strong
          >. I don’t just think about features. I think about decisions,
          behaviors, barriers, adoption, and long-term value.
        </p>

        <p
          class="font-heading text-base leading-[1.85] font-light text-white/80"
        >
          I care about <strong class="font-bold"
            >what gets built, why it matters, and who benefits from it.</strong
          >
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div>
    <OrbitalDiagram />
  </div>
</section>
